2. Why standards work

Standards don’t force identical perception.

They create alignment anchors.

Examples:
	•	time standards → we can meet
	•	language → we can transmit meaning
	•	money → we can exchange value
	•	APIs → systems can interoperate
	•	protocols → networks function
	•	measurement → science accumulates

Each one reduces interpretation entropy.

